From 32ffef2402f75e49ff2d606cf1eed379ee229f31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 29 Sep 2025 12:26:18 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Enable AFC response retrieval to 
 restore SP power mode after 'wifi' command

When the 'wifi' command is issued, the firmware remains active, but
hostapd restarts and loses the AFC response, causing the AP
to fall back to LPI power mode. However, the ath12k driver and
cfg80211 layer retain the AFC payload, as confirmed by SP channel
availability in 'iw reg get'.

Introduce the vendor command QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_AFC_FETCH_POWER_EVENT
to address this issue. Upon hostapd restart, if a 6 GHz interface
is configured and SP channels are detected via
hostapd_setup_interface_complete_sync, hostapd queries the driver
for the AFC response using this command and the attribute
QCA_WLAN_VENDOR_ATTR_CONFIG_RADIO_INDEX.

Implement hostapd_fetch_afc_power_event to retrieve
the AFC response synchronously. Process the response using
qca_nl80211_handle_afc_events, enabling the AP to select the
best power mode and transition to SP mode if available.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: AFC
Patch-dependency:
r66-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Handle-AFC-Channel-Change.patch
